<LENGTH>
<P>
200 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Babette's Feast (Bravo Sunday at 5 p.m.): Subtle, amusing Isak Dinesen tale 
starring Stephane Audran as a selfless servant who offers an astonishing gift 
of gratitude to her employers, a pair of elderly sisters. (1:40) 
</P>
<P>
Modern Romance (Channel 13 Tuesday at noon): Albert Brooks' 1981 romantic 
comedy, in which he casts himself as a Hollywood film editor so totally 
enamored of an attractive bank official (Kathryn Harrold) that he makes their 
lives miserable with his possessiveness and jealousy. A fresh and acute vision 
of life and of self from a distinctive talent. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Footlight Parade (Channel 5 Thursday at 3:15 a.m.): Zesty classic Warners 
musical starring James Cagney and featuring many Busby Berkeley numbers. (2:15) 
</P>
<P>
Studs Lonigan (A&amp;E Friday at 1 a.m.): Ambitious 1960 attempt to film the 
James T. Farrell novel of the 1920s, directed by Irving Lerner and adapted and 
produced by Philip Yordan. Christopher Knight stars; Jack Nicholson has a small 
role. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Monterey Pop (Channel 28 Saturday at 12:30 a.m.): The first important rock 
concert film is still one of the best, a record of the historic 1967 gathering 
featuring Jimi Hendrix, Janis Joplin and many others. (1:30) 
</P>
</TEXT>
