<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIRAMI SU ; 
</P>
<P>
IT'S THE MARSCARPONE AND LADYFINGER DESSERT YOU SEE EVERYWHERE. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buon Gusto, 3110 Main St., Santa Monica. (213) 452-4288. Style: Mainstream 
modern, known for remarkable desserts. Setting: Pilasters, posters, paintings 
and precious patio. Tirami Su: $4. 
</P>
<P>
Fresco, 514 S. Brand Blvd., Glendale. (818) 247-5541. Style: Serious contender 
for best Valley restaurant. Setting: Courtyard with skylight and fake ivy. 
Tirami Su: $5. 
</P>
<P>
Il Tigullio, 8771 W. Pico Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 273-1166. Style: Haute in a 
hut. Setting: Shoebox with green awning out on the sidewalk. Tirami Su: $4.50. 
</P>
<P>
La Pergola, 15005 Ventura Blvd., Sherman Oaks. (818) 905-8402. Style: 
Neighborhood Italian in the spirit of the new Northern tradition. Setting: 
Off-white stucco walls with plenty of plants in plastic pots. Tirami Su: $3.50. 
</P>
<P>
Tuttopasta, 417 S. Hill St., Los Angeles. (213) 621-2625. Style: Stepchild of 
trendy Tuttobene. Setting: Pure plastic set in old Subway Terminal building. 
Tirami Su: $2.50. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
