Photo, COLOR, Tomato-Sirloin Soup, left, from Sonora Cafe's Felix Salcedo pairs 
with an herb- and cheese-filled quesadilla. Joachim Splichal of Patina created 
a vegetable-filled corn chowder, top right, to accompany a rich skewered shrimp 
sandwich. At Five Feet in Orange County, Michael Kang chose a light chicken 
broth with vegetables and goat cheese-filled won tons, right, to serve with 
hearty scallion pancakes filled with smoked duck, shiitake mushrooms. ANN 
MITCHELL 
</P>
