<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLASH FROM THE PAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When Arcadia was incorporated in 1903, one of the first orders of business for 
city officials was to issue a liquor license to Clara Baldwin Stocker, daughter 
of San Gabriel Valley land baron Elias Jackson (Lucky) Baldwin, for her saloon, 
Clara Villa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
