<TEXT>
<P>
Dan Nelson did not touch on two questions I have: 
</P>
<P>
1. Does not the appraiser deliberately "low-ball" his estimates because he is 
employed by the mortgage lender and not the buyer/sellers? That has been my 
experience and also others with whom I've spoken. 
</P>
<P>
2. Mr. Nelson's description of how he arrives at an estimate would seem to have 
an obvious flaw. Namely, when demand is pushing prices up, his technique of 
setting a value purely on what has previously transpired flies in the face of 
reality. 
