<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAIN CORNER: LUFTHANSA AND KLM OFFER INCENTIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lufthansa again is offering a complimentary Avis rental car for one week to 
passengers flying round trip from the United States to Frankfurt. The offer is 
good from now through March 31, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Two people have to fly together between Sunday and Thursday, paying any of 
Lufthansa's regular fares, excluding its nonrefundable Special Saver fare. The 
offer is good, however, with the airline's APEX fare. 
</P>
<P>
Reservations for the car have to be made at least 14 days before departure, 
with Lufthansa taking care of the booking. You can pick up the car at the 
airports in Frankfurt, Munich, Vienna and 15 other German and Austrian cities. 
Have your Lufthansa ticket ready to show at the Avis counter. 
</P>
<P>
The offer includes unlimited mileage and the value-added tax in both West 
Germany and Austria. In addition, you have free drop-off privileges when you 
return the car to an Avis station served by Lufthansa, as long as it's in the 
same country in which you picked up the auto. 
</P>
<P>
Another off-season offer comes from KLM. If you fly round trip to Amsterdam on 
the Dutch airline, you're entitled to the Happy Holland Bargain. This offers 
you your first night's accommodation in Amsterdam for $20 to $40 per person 
based on double occupancy, depending on the hotel. Continental breakfast is 
included, along with taxes and service charges. One child under 12 is free when 
sharing the room with two adults. 
</P>
<P>
If you're traveling solo, you can get rooms from $30 to $70. 
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one hotels, mostly in downtown Amsterdam, are participating in the 
program. The offer is good until April 1, 1990. The hotel booking should be 
made in the United States, and can be processed by KLM at the time of the air 
booking. 
</P>
<P>
Contact Lufthansa at toll-free (800) 645-3880 and KLM at (800) 777-5553. JACK 
ADLER 
</P>
