<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN ALLA BREVE MEDLEY: LAZAROF: "MUSIC FOR STRINGS." CHAMBER MUSIC/LA. LAUREL 
RECORDS LR-843CD (COMPACT DISC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By John Henken 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Serenade for String Sextet (1985) and the String Octet "La Laurenziana" 
(1987) -- both premiered in Los Angeles -- frame the disc. Both are big, 
three-movement works of characteristically intense sonorities and complex, 
varied textures, and both offer ample opportunities for tightly meshed 
virtuosity. The performances, under Lazarof's direction, are incisively paced 
chains of explosions. Also included are the String Quartet from 1980, and 
Chamber Music/LA director Yukiko Kamei's soaring, probing account of the Lyric 
Suite for Solo Violin (1983). John Henken 
</P>
