<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN ALLA BREVE MEDLEY: GLASS: "SONGS FROM THE TRILOGY." 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By John Henken 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Douglas Perry and Paul Esswood, countertenors; The Philip Glass Ensemble; N.Y. 
City Opera Orchestra &amp; Chorus, conducted by Christopher Keene; Stuttgart 
State Opera Orchestra &amp; Chorus, conducted by Dennis Russell Davies. CBS MK 
45580 (compact disc). The juxtapositions on this collection of greatest hits 
from "Einstein on the Beach," "Satyagraha" and "Akhnaten" put the changes in 
Glass' style in high relief, and underscore the different philosophical bases 
of the three operas. It will probably change few minds about the music, 
although only the most confirmed Glassiphobe could resist the otherworldly 
beauty of the modal close-harmony in the Akhnaten/Nefertiti duet. The sounds 
have transfered well from their original formats. John Henken 
