<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN KILLED DESTROYING OLD EXPLOSIVE AGENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BIWABIK, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man burning old explosive agents was killed and a fellow worker seriously 
injured Friday in a blast felt by residents as far as two miles away, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The explosion left a hole about 15 feet across at the site of the fire, a few 
hundred yards from a Nitro-Chem plant, which manufactures explosives for mining 
companies, authorities said. The cause of the blast was under investigation. 
</P>
