<HEADLINE>
<P>
IDEA IS IN THE BAG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the issue of paper vs. plastic shopping bags, I would suggest neither 
("Big Bear Packages a Worthy Concept," Oct. 29). European shoppers generally 
bring along their own shopping bags, which are usually made of a lightweight 
see-through nylon netting. The bags fold up into a small wad in pocket or 
purse. This practice has got to save the stores a bundle. Perhaps some 
enterprising company could give away such bags free to shoppers with their 
logo, and stores might give some coupons to shoppers who bring their own bags 
as an added incentive. 
</P>
<P>
GENE BURKARD 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
