Photo, COLOR, Apple grower Don Heinicke. UPSETTING THE APPLE CART Since the 
controversy over the chemical ripener Alar nine months ago, apple growers are 
struggling to get in profitable crops without it.; Photo, Don Heinicke on the 
288-acre Cascade Foothills orchard near the Columbia River: "The lack of Alar 
has hurt us." ; Photo, Ed Colpitts stretches to reach Red Delicious apples, the 
last of the season, at Cascade Foothills orchard. ; Photo, Red Delicious apples 
