<P>
Business owners and residents of St. Croix protested President Bush's plan to 
withdraw 1,100 federal troops that were sent to the island to quell looting 
following Hurricane Hugo. The United Concerned Citizens of St. Croix said it 
joined the Chamber of Commerce and the Board of Realtors to lobby the White 
