<TEXT>
<P>
FREEWAYS -- Assemblyman Richard Katz (D-Sylmar), chairman of the Assembly 
Transportation Committee, will hold a special hearing Tuesday at the Los 
Angeles City Board of Public Works office regarding the seismic safety of 
California's freeway system. Specific attention will be given to Los 
Angeles-area bridges and overpasses. 
</P>
<P>
ELECTION DAY -- Voters will go to the polls from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. on Tuesday to 
elect City Council members and decide local ballot issues in 14 cities across 
Los Angeles County. Elections are also scheduled in 68 school districts, eight 
water districts, one library district and a road financing authority. One 
election in Hermosa Beach will determine whether dogs can run free in a new 
city park. 
