<P>
Photo, Sherman Oaks residents urge passers-by to sign petitions against the 
proposed complex at Ventura Boulevard and Woodman Avenue. CARLOS CHAVEZ / Los 
Angeles Times; Photo, Committee head Judith McCurdy criticized developer, 
saying: "Silence seems to be the way they do business, even with the city." 
</P>
