<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 HELD IN SLAYING OF MAN IN CANOGA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested 27-year-old Antonio Cardenas on suspicion of murder in 
connection with the shooting of a 26-year-old man who was found dead in an 
apartment in the 23000 block of Cohasset Street in Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
Armando Santacruz Becerra was found shot to death at the apartment at 11:30 
a.m. Saturday, when police responded to a report of shots being fired, 
according to Officer Don Matthews of the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Cardenas and Francisco Cisneros, 20, were hospitalized in unknown condition 
with gunshot wounds, Matthews said. Matthews declined to say to what hospital 
the two had been taken. 
</P>
<P>
Police were seeking 26-year-old Ricardo Villasenor Becerra for questioning in 
connection with the shooting, Matthews said. 
</P>
<P>
According to police reports, Armando Santacruz Becerra and Cisneros were 
arguing with Cardenas and Ricardo Villasenor Becerra, when the shooting 
occurred. 
</P>
