<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. QUAKE: SPECIAL REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scientists are certain that a major earthquake will hit Southern California 
sometime in the future, but they do not know precisely when or where it will 
strike. A Times Special Report, "Waiting for the Quake," provides a detailed 
look at the earthquake faults that criss-cross the Los Angeles area and 
examines two leading scenarios for a big quake. It also shows which freeways 
and key buildings are vulnerable, and tells how residents can prepare for the 
Big One. See Section Q. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA110589-0180 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 130551 </DOCID>
