<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 10; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
107 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAILEY SETS YARDAGE MARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ABILENE, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Johnny Bailey of Texas A&amp;I broke the NCAA all-purpose yardage record in the 
Javelinas' 33-13 victory over Abilene Christian on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Bailey broke the record, which combines rushing, receiving and return yardage, 
of 7,623 yards with a 19-yard kickoff return. The record had been held by Kenny 
Gamble, who played for Colgate from 1984-87. 
</P>
<P>
The kickoff return, with 6:08 remaining in the second quarter, gave Bailey 
7,637 all-purpose career yards. Bailey, a 5-foot-9, 180-pound running back, 
finished with 179 rushing yards in 23 carries and 41 yards in two returns for 
7,726 all-purpose yards. He has one regular-season game remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
