<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CSUN ADVANCES TO SEMIFINALS OF VOLLEYBALL EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge women's volleyball team advanced to the semifinals of 
the Air Force Academy's Premier Tournament in Colorado Springs by defeating Cal 
Poly Pomona and Cal State Bakersfield on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Matadors, ranked seventh in the nation in the latest National 
Collegiate Athletic Assn. Division II poll, beat Pomona, 15-6, 15-3, 15-7, then 
downed Bakersfield in the quarterfinals, 15-5, 9-15, 15-11, 15-3. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (22-9 overall) has won 10 straight matches and will meet UC 
Riverside today. Cal State Sacramento will meet West Texas State in the other 
semifinal match. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Cross-Country 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran's men's and women's cross-country teams both placed fourth in the 
National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics District III championships in 
La Mirada. 
</P>
<P>
In the men's competition, Pt. Loma Nazarene finished first with 38 points, 
followed by Fresno Pacific (67), Westmont (80) and Cal Lutheran (88). 
</P>
<P>
Westmont finished first in the women's competition with 53 points, followed by 
Pt. Loma Nazarane (59), Azusa Pacific (65) and Cal Lutheran (110). 
</P>
</TEXT>
