<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAITING FOR THE QUAKE; 
</P>
<P>
CALTRANS' LIST OF 44 TROUBLESPOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
These are the bridges in the Los Angeles County area that have been designated 
by the California Department of Transportation as mostly like to sustain damage 
in an earthquake. They have been given top priority in a retrofitting program 
designed to strengthen the ability of their columns to withstand severe 
groundshaking. The risk rating the department has assigned to each bridge is 
based on a scale of 0.00 to 1.00, with 0.00 the least vulnerable and 1.00 the 
most vulnerable. The list represents only single column bridges. A program to 
retrofit multi-column bridges is expected to begin soon. 
</P>
