<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dana Point Planning Commission will hold a public hearing Tuesday on a 
proposal by the Stein-Brief Group Inc., which hopes to build its headquarters 
on the northwest corner of Ritz-Carlton Drive and Coast Highway. 
</P>
<P>
Stein-Brief proposes building a "modernistic structure" with two levels of 
subterranean parking. The structure, designed by Chicago architect Helmut Jahn, 
would have an exposed steel frame with sides of teak and clear glass. 
</P>
<P>
The public hearing will begin at 7 p.m. at 34052 Del Obispo St. 
</P>
